HEADWORD: Khaya
<hw>Kha"ya</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
lofty West African tree (<spn>Khaya Senegalensis</spn>), related to the
mahogany, which it resembles in the quality of the wood. The bark is
used as a febrifuge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

